28/04/2006
ZAGREB Croatia -- Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic met with Finnish counterpart Erkki Tuomioja on Thursday (27 April) in Zagreb.
EU enlargement, Croatia's bid for EU membership and bilateral relations were the focus of discussions.
The talks also covered Croatia's initiative for the expansion of CEFTA as a framework for multilateral co-operation in Southeast Europe, and Croatia's preparations for chairmanship of the South-East European Co-operation Process.
Tuomioja said he was satisfied with the progress of Croatia's accession negotiations with the European Commission.
Finland assumes the rotating EU presidency from Austria on 1 July.
(HINA - 27/04/06)
